    "solution_explanation": "There are 7! permutations of the digits 1 through 7. If the string 153 occurs, treat it as one block; then the number of permutations is 5!. If the string 2467 occurs, treat it as one block; then the number is 4!. If both occur, we have two blocks, so the count is 2!. By inclusion-exclusion, the required number is 7! - 5! - 4! + 2! = 5040 - 120 - 24 + 2 = 4898.",
