    "legacy_publish_id": "imppub_1772719448537",
    "solution_explanation": "If all 5 boys sit together, treat them as one block with the 4 girls, giving 5! arrangements of the 5 entities and 5! internal arrangements of the boys: 5!·5! = 14400. If no two boys sit together, first arrange the 4 girls in 4! ways; this creates 5 slots, and the 5 boys must occupy all 5 of them in 5! ways. That gives 4!·5! = 2880. The two cases are disjoint, so the total is 14400 + 2880 = 17280.",
    "manual_solution_latex": "Case 1: all $5$ boys sit together.\nTreat the boys as one block. Then we have $5$ entities in a row, so the number of arrangements is\n\\[5!\\cdot 5!=14400.\\]\nCase 2: no two boys sit together.\nArrange the $4$ girls first in $4!$ ways. This creates $5$ slots, and the $5$ boys must occupy all $5$ slots in $5!$ ways. Hence the number of arrangements is\n\\[4!\\cdot 5!=2880.\\]\nThese two cases are disjoint, so the total number of arrangements is\n\\[14400+2880=17280.\\]",
